Contact Services specializes in downhole products and services for chemical injection solutions, including capillary tubing, capillary inspections, cable spooling, and material Founded as a capillary tubing service company, Management took a conservative approach to adding new service lines, making sure we had mastered capillary tubing before adding the cable spooling service line, and ultimately the capillary inspection service CAPILLARY TUBING Capillary tubing allows customers to deliver downhole chemical treatment programs with pinpoint This ensures that % of the chemical is delivered to the correct point and eliminates the concern for annular pressures inhibiting delivery, which is a problem for many standard backside chemical ‚Äôs capillary trailers are capable of: Pumping third party chemicals Proactive flushes to mitigate capillary plugging when ESPs falter ¬≠Pumping on the fly, both while pulling and running in the hole Pressure testing up to 6,000 psi Completing wellbore capillary flushes CABLE SPOOLING The cable spooling trailers have been retrofitted to accommodate the region‚Äôs demanding surface level and deep wellbore The trailers have been retrofitted with drive motors that offer the torque and the speed to handle any job (both pulls and installations) safely and The Company‚Äôs field service technicians perform the lay down of ESP equipment and generate the lay down reports for all major OEM manufacturers ¬≠The cable spooling trailers are equipped with onboard air compressors for the installation of equipment banding as well as clamps from all leading manufacturers: Slingco, Cannon, Winterhawk, Hulk and Grippy clamps The trailers are also equipped with splice tables for cable repairs onsite CAPILLARY TUBING INSPECTIONS In addition to the capillary EATING WELL RESOURCES BLOG How Kidneys Work Kidneys are organs, about the size of your Most people are born with two of them, and they can be found on either side of your spine, just below your rib They keep you healthy in a variety of ways, but the important thing to remember is their main job: to keep your body‚Äôs chemicals in They do this by filtering waste and toxins out of your blood, and then creating the urine that will carry these wastes out of your All told, your kidneys filter about quarts of blood and produce 1 to 2 quarts of urine every How Filtering Happens Your kidneys aren‚Äôt just one big Instead, that work is done by about 1 million microscopic parts called The filtering part of the nephron, called the glomerulus, takes in blood and removes fluid and waste products from The glomerulus then passes the waste fluid on through the tubule, another part of the The tubule continues the filtering process by sending needed minerals back into What‚Äôs left after that is urine, which the tubule passes into the ureter, where it will travel into the When Kidneys Stop Working When your kidneys get damaged by disease, these parts can‚Äôt function like they This is called kidney It can lead to a build up of toxins in your blood, which can be very Unfortunately, there‚Äôs no turning back the clock on chronic kidney disease ‚Äî it‚Äôs not possible to repair the damage That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs important to take very good care of your kidneys ‚Äî or get dialysis or a transplant, if they‚Äôre damaged beyond What is Chronic Kidney Disease? Chronic kidney disease (CKD) is when your kidneys can‚Äôt filter waste and toxins as well as they It‚Äôs a gradual process that can eventually lead to kidney failure ‚Äî and unfortunately, once it begins, it‚Äôs But that doesn‚Äôt mean that there‚Äôs nothing you can No matter what stage of CKD you‚Äôre in, committing to your care can slow its progression, and keep your kidneys functioning as long as There‚Äôs no one cause of CKD ‚Äî but in most cases, it‚Äôs related to diabetes and high blood Age plays a role as well people over are at an increased risk for Genes, too, are a factor, which may be part of why African Americans, Hispanics, and Native Americans are at the greatest risk for developing CKD progresses in 5 stages, with stage 5 being the most It entails near total failure of your kidneys and is otherwise known as end stage renal disease (ESRD). The symptoms of the early stages of CKD are very subtle and difficult to detect ‚Äî so it‚Äôs important to get screened for it if you have any of the risk factors mentioned And if the day comes when you do enter stage 5, you can seek dialysis or a kidney transplant to give yourself the best possible quality of Stages of Chronic Kidney Disease Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) is a progressive It develops in 5 stages, as kidney function gradually By stage 5, the final stage of CKD, the kidneys are typically approaching complete CKD can almost never be But patients in the early stages of the disease can do a lot to slow this progression That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs important to understand how CKD affects your Getting tested, diagnosed, and treated early can add years of healthy kidney function to your How do I know what stage of CKD I‚Äôm in? Each of CKD‚Äôs five stages are divided by how well your kidneys In the first three stages of CKD, symptoms are very You may not notice any physical changes at But if you have high blood pressure, or if you have irregular unrinalysis , your doctor may want to test for kidney The best measure of this is called the Glomerular Filtration Rate (GFR). Glomeruli are the tiny blood vessels that do most of the filtering work in your kidneys ‚Äî so the GFR is measuring how well they do their Your doctor can perform a blood test to find out what your estimated GFR (or eGFR) A higher eGFR means better kidney Below, you can see the eGFR measures associated with each stag

Each investment project has a funding target that has been determined by the project owner, but the final combined investment made may be more than the target amount based on the success of the raise and the other capital commitments of the project EquityDoor‚Äôs escrow service typically will not collect funds until the project is approaching the time of the expected If the project falls significantly short of attaining targeted funding, or the transaction otherwise fails to close, % of your investment commitment will be returned to you . If there is a material change to the terms of an offering or to the information provided by the issuer, EquityDoor must notify investors of the material change and each investor must reconfirm his or her investment commitment within five business days of receipt of the If an investor fails to reconfirm his or her investment commitment with those five business days, EquityDoor will direct the refund of investor EquityDoor can not guarantee the performance of any There is always the risk that returns may fail to meet projected amounts and even that investors may lose all of their invested Investors should review closely the information provided on each investment opportunity that is of interest, including the ‚Äúrisk factors‚Äù described in the investor package of legal Are there a minimum investment amounts? M A BILITY All physical and cognitive abilities are respected and welcomed at The Village of Hope, so whether you experience a degree of limitation or you feel unstoppable, there is a home for you ‚Äã G ENERATIONAL From college students who are finding their way in life, to young families with active children to elders who have seen it all, the Village of Hope community is enriched by the perspectives and needs of people of different ‚Äã I NCLUSIVE Traditional senior communities exclude the young and nursing homes exclude those who are Loved ones are separated when a spouse needing nursing moves for care and adult family members are denied the ability to live with the individual and help with the Village of Hope creates a thriving community because it embraces people with different life ‚Äã C Our vision of strikes a balance between community and Some living arrangements lack sufficient privacy and others offer little or no sense of Village of Hope, in contrast, offers people a home of their own and the opportunity to share in community meals, fellowship, learning, and a host of activities as This is a place where people can have good neighbors, be a good neighbor, but have a safe retreat with autonomous ‚Äã Village of Hope recognizes that there is truly ‚Äúnothing new under the sun‚Äù but what has changed is the degree to which the extended family unit now serves as the conduit for In rural communities across America, people are having fewer children and they are living farther away from their parents than ever If we are willing to open our minds to new ways of living, and connecting to others, new possibilities begin to It is a paradigm shift, a model for the About Us: Village of Hope, is a project of Mature Resources Foundation a charitable organization, and is supported by the Clearfield County Area Agency on Aging, Get In Touch: Like us on Facebook ! (814) ‚Äã   Village Hall | Village of Hope About Us MAGIC Community Village Hall Timeline of Events VoH Donate News Our Team Testimonials Gallery Contact Us Master Plan Book More Use tab to navigate through the menu VILLAGE HALL Food and Fellowship ‚Äã Who doesn t enjoy good company and a delicious meal? At Village of Hope, we believe that fellowship is important to help individuals learn, grow and thrive from the support and relationships gained in these It is especially vital for older adults to have this opportunity, as far too many of our seniors take every meal The Village Hall creates the physical structure needed to build social structures around the experience of sharing good food in good From potlucks, picnics, to celebratory banquets or funeral buffets, we need a local gathering place that can serve the community through food and Delicious and nutritious meals will be served in the Village Hall, thanks to a partnership with Morrison Living . Not only will Morrison Living serve individuals at Village of Hope, , but it will be open to the community as Art and Music ‚Äã ‚Äã At Village of Hope, we believe the need to express ourselves creatively is important and that is why we incorporate art and music into our We see the Mountain Arts as tools of healing for people and their Mountain Arts are defined as forms of creative expression that people in rural communities grew up with and know This includes songs, images and stories that told people who they were and why the world is the way it Health and Wellness Medical care is a very powerful tool and it is crucial that residents have access to the best available Rural communities have had difficulty accessing the most expert care and Village of Hope, will change that by bringing access to leading health care These health care systems will provide telehealth and telepresence technologies within the Village Hall, so residents don t have to travel Susquehanna Wellness Clinic will serve as a vital resource to Village of Hope, ‚Äã A community in nature, Village of Hope is a space to connect with nature and stay in shape Village of Hope, features a number of green spaces and miles of space to get moving and get connected with others of the Lighting Safety and security are at the top of our priorities and lighting is just one of the ways we embody Lighting fixtures at Village of Hope, are thoughtfully placed in locations that aid in ease of access around the This design is especially helpful to elders of the community, as it lights areas of walking spaces which are often of concern to this ‚Äã About Us: Village of Hope, is a project of Mature Resources Foundation a charitable organization, and is supported by the Clearfield County Area Agency on Aging, Get In Touch: Like us on Facebook ! There are alternative insurance policies you might be able to qualify for coverage Next, there is another factor you need to consider while making insurance decisions is that guaranteed issue life insurance policies are normally for smaller benefit amounts than comparable life insurance Usually, the policies issued for death benefits are between $5,000 and $50 This might be exactly what you are looking But if it‚Äôs not, that‚Äôs another reason why it‚Äôs important to consider all your options and ask a specialist about other life insurance Why Guaranteed Issue Life Insurance Might Be The Right Fit For Typically, Guaranteed Issue life insurance is recommended for people who can‚Äôt qualify for traditional fully underwritten insurance This is usually a result of health, lifestyle, or other Coverage is guaranteed for life, regardless of those This can save your loved ones from having to pay for final expenses or any other expenses after you‚Äôre While this is not the only option, this can be a good option for you if you are HIV+ and need life insurance .
